.TH IDISPLAYFONT 1 "June 2026" "ilib @ILIB_VERSION@" "Ilib Manual"
.SH NAME
idisplayfont \- render an X11 BDF font's glyph table to an image
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B idisplayfont
.RB [ \-gif | \-png | \-ppm ]
.RB [ \-hex | \-dec ]
.I font.bdf
.B >
.I out.img
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B idisplayfont
loads the X11 BDF font
.I font.bdf
and writes an image to standard output showing each glyph in a labeled grid,
which is handy for previewing a font. The character codes labeling each cell
are shown in decimal by default.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-ppm
Write PPM/PNM output (this is the default).
.TP
.B \-png
Write PNG output (requires Ilib built with libpng).
.TP
.B \-gif
Write GIF output (requires Ilib built with giflib).
.TP
.B \-dec
Label glyph cells with decimal character codes (default).
.TP
.B \-hex
Label glyph cells with hexadecimal character codes.
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.nf
idisplayfont -png /usr/local/share/ilib/fonts/courR10.bdf > courR10.png
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success, or 1 on an unrecognized option, a missing font
argument, a load error, or a request for a format the library was not built
with.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ifont2h (1),
.BR iconvert (1)
.PP
Full API documentation: https://craigk5n.github.io/ilib/
